						               													<description>The game is based on the invention and narration of strange and bizarre stories, from the cards that come out, corresponding to the questions: &amp;ldquo;Where?&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;Who?&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;What?&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;To Who?&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;With What? it's because?&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In this expansion &amp;ldquo;O Homem que Mordeu o C&amp;atilde;o: Esc&amp;acirc;ndalos&amp;rdquo;, players set out in search of even more bizarre and scandalous stories to tell, at the right time, and make their listeners laugh. &amp;#10;There are many possibilities! Put creativity to the test.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game can be played on the main game board or individually.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Using as an expansion, the rules of the board game will be used.&amp;#10;Using only this box, our board will be replaced by two special dice.&amp;#10;The &amp;quot;Action&amp;quot; dice will be rolled and we will do whatever it takes on the face of that dice. &amp;quot;Star&amp;quot;, forces us to tell the story in front of us, steal letters from another player, be punished by the other players in our next narration, or maybe change the theme and then we launch the second dice to see which theme will be changed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We have time counted by the hourglass and if we get away with it and manage to convince the other players, we earn a prestigious coin.&amp;#10;At the end of the game, the player with the most prestigious coins wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
